==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tuckahoe
<hw>Tuck"a*hoe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[North American
Indian, bread.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A curious vegetable
production of the Southern Atlantic United States, growing under ground
like a truffle and often attaining immense size. The real nature is
unknown. Called also <altname>Indian bread</altname>, and
<altname>Indian loaf</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tucker</ent>⟦br⟧
